
# ğŸ“˜ Handy Notes on Maven

## â­ 1. What is Maven?
Maven is a **build automation and project management tool** for Java.  
It helps with:
- Building the project  
- Managing dependencies  
- Following a standard structure  
- Packaging (JAR/WAR)  
- Running tests  
- Deployment  

## â­ 2. Why Maven?
- âœ” Automatically downloads jars  
- âœ” Standard directory layout  
- âœ” Same build on all systems  
- âœ” Powerful plugin system  
- âœ” Easy to build, test, package, deploy  

## â­ 3. Maven Standard Directory Structure
```
project/
 â”œâ”€â”€ src/
 â”‚    â”œâ”€â”€ main/
 â”‚    â”‚     â”œâ”€â”€ java/
 â”‚    â”‚     â”œâ”€â”€ resources/
 â”‚    â””â”€â”€ test/
 â”‚          â”œâ”€â”€ java/
 â”‚          â”œâ”€â”€ resources/
 â”œâ”€â”€ pom.xml
```

## â­ 4. What is `pom.xml`?
**POM = Project Object Model**
Defines:
- Project details  
- Dependencies  
- Build plugins  
- Repository information  

### Basic Example
```xml
<project>
  <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>
  <groupId>com.example</groupId>
  <artifactId>demo-project</artifactId>
  <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
  <dependencies>
    <dependency>
      <groupId>junit</groupId>
      <artifactId>junit</artifactId>
      <version>4.13.2</version>
      <scope>test</scope>
    </dependency>
  </dependencies>
</project>
```

## â­ 5. Important Maven Terminology
| Term | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| GroupId | Package or organization name |
| ArtifactId | Name of the project |
| Version | Project version |
| Dependencies | External libraries |
| Plugins | Adds extra build features |

## â­ 6. Maven Lifecycle
### Clean Lifecycle
- `mvn clean` â†’ Removes `target/`

### Default (Build) Lifecycle
| Command | Action |
|--------|--------|
| mvn compile | Compiles source files |
| mvn test | Runs tests |
| mvn package | Creates JAR/WAR |
| mvn install | Installs into local repo |
| mvn deploy | Deploys to remote repo |

### Site Lifecycle
- `mvn site` â†’ Generates documentation

## â­ 7. Maven Archetypes
Templates for creating new projects.
```
mvn archetype:generate -DgroupId=com.example -DartifactId=myapp -DarchetypeArtifactId=maven-archetype-quickstart -DinteractiveMode=false
```

## â­ 8. Dependency Scope
| Scope | Used For |
|-------|----------|
| compile | Default; needed everywhere |
| test | Only for tests |
| provided | Provided by servers |
| runtime | Needed only at runtime |
| system | Local jars with path |

## â­ 9. Maven Repositories
- **Local:** `~/.m2/repository`  
- **Central:** Maven's global repo  
- **Remote:** Nexus / Artifactory  

## â­ 10. Useful Maven Commands
| Command | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| mvn clean | Delete target folder |
| mvn compile | Compile code |
| mvn test | Run tests |
| mvn package | Build JAR/WAR |
| mvn install | Add to local repo |
| mvn dependency:tree | View dependencies |
| mvn clean install -DskipTests | Build without tests |

## â­ 11. Common Plugins
### Compiler Plugin
```xml
<plugin>
  <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
  <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>
  <version>3.8.1</version>
  <configuration>
     <source>1.8</source>
     <target>1.8</target>
  </configuration>
</plugin>
```

## â­ 12. Multi-Module Project
```xml
<modules>
  <module>service</module>
  <module>web</module>
  <module>dao</module>
</modules>
```

## ğŸ¯ Quick Summary
- Maven = Build + Dependency management  
- POM = Configuration file  
- Archetypes = Templates  
- Commands = clean, compile, package  
- Scopes = compile, test, provided, runtime  
